This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on December 6, 2017. The memorandum is titled "Suspension of Limitations under the Jerusalem Embassy Act" and is directed to the Secretary of State. 

In the memorandum, President Trump invokes his authority as President and states that it is necessary to suspend, for a period of 6 months, the limitations set forth in sections 3(b) and 7(b) of the Jerusalem Embassy Act of 1995. The Act pertains to the relocation of the U.S. embassy in Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.

The President determines that this suspension is necessary to protect the national security interests of the United States. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to transmit this determination, along with a report, to Congress and publish it in the Federal Register. The suspension will take effect after the determination and report are transmitted to Congress.